## Focus Areas

### 1. Accessibility - Perceivable

**Text Alternatives**
- Images have meaningful alt text
- Decorative images have empty alt=""
- Icons have accessible labels
- Complex graphics have descriptions
- SVGs have title/desc or aria-label

**Color & Contrast**
- Text meets contrast ratios (4.5:1 normal, 3:1 large)
- Not relying on color alone to convey information
- Status indicators have text/icon in addition to color
- Focus indicators visible
- Error states not just red color

**Content Structure**
- Logical heading hierarchy (h1 > h2 > h3)
- Lists used for list content
- Tables have headers
- Landmark regions defined
- Reading order makes sense

**Responsive & Scalable**
- Text resizable to 200% without loss
- Content reflows on small screens
- Touch targets adequate size (44x44px)
- No horizontal scrolling at 320px width

---

### 2. Accessibility - Operable

**Keyboard Navigation**
- All interactive elements keyboard accessible
- Visible focus indicators on all elements
- Logical tab order
- No keyboard traps
- Skip links for navigation
- Shortcuts don't conflict with browser/AT shortcuts

**Focus Management**
- Focus moves to modal when opened
- Focus returns to trigger when modal closes
- Focus moves to new content when loaded
- Focus not lost during interactions
- Focus visible during all states

**Timing & Motion**
- Users can pause/stop auto-updating content
- No content flashes more than 3 times per second
- Animations respect prefers-reduced-motion
- Timeouts can be extended
- No time limits on critical actions

**Navigation**
- Multiple ways to find content
- Clear breadcrumbs
- Consistent navigation location
- Current page indicated in navigation

---

### 3. Accessibility - Understandable

**Readable Content**
- Language of page specified
- Abbreviations explained
- Jargon minimized or explained
- Instructions clear
- Error messages helpful

**Predictable Behavior**
- No unexpected context changes
- Consistent component behavior
- Actions clearly labeled
- Form submission explicit

**Input Assistance**
- Labels associated with inputs
- Required fields indicated
- Input format requirements stated
- Errors identified and described
- Suggestions for correction provided

---

### 4. Accessibility - Robust

**ARIA Usage**
- ARIA only when HTML semantics insufficient
- Correct ARIA roles, states, properties
- ARIA labels for custom components
- Live regions for dynamic content
- No conflicting ARIA

**Component Patterns**
- Standard patterns for common widgets
- Disclosure widgets (accordion, dropdown)
- Modal dialogs
- Tabs and tab panels
- Menus and menu items
- Trees and tree items

**Screen Reader Support**
- Content announced in logical order
- Dynamic updates announced
- Status messages communicated
- Form validation announced
- Progress announced

---

### 5. User Experience - States

**Loading States**
- Loading indicators for async operations
- Skeleton loaders for content areas
- Progress indicators for long operations
- Blocking UI during critical operations
- Non-blocking for background operations

**Empty States**
- Clear explanation of why empty
- Guidance on what to do next
- Call-to-action to add content
- Appropriate illustration or icon
- No broken layouts

**Error States**
- Clear error message
- What went wrong
- How to fix it
- Action to retry or recover
- Maintain user's work/progress

**Success States**
- Confirmation of completed action
- What happens next
- Clear next steps
- Appropriate feedback duration

---

### 6. User Experience - Interactions

**Forms**
- Clear field labels
- Placeholder text is supplementary, not replacement for labels
- Help text for complex fields
- Inline validation (on blur, not on type)
- Clear error state per field
- Disabled submit until valid (or clear validation on submit)
- Success confirmation after submit

**Modals & Dialogs**
- Clear title describing purpose
- Focused content, minimal distractions
- Clear primary and secondary actions
- Cancel/close always available
- Escape key closes modal
- Click outside behavior consistent
- Mobile-friendly sizing

**Tables & Lists**
- Clear column headers
- Sortable columns indicated
- Pagination for long lists
- Empty state for no results
- Actions easily discoverable
- Row selection clear

**Navigation & Wayfinding**
- Current location clear
- Breadcrumbs for deep navigation
- Back navigation works
- Deep links work
- Browser history managed correctly

